@phase-1 @feat-lca @tutoring-loop @adapters
Feature: MCP LLM Player and Coach Adapters
  As the Study Tutor MCP server
  I want production LLMPlayerAdapter and LLMCoachAdapter wired into a
    per-turn PlayerCoachOrchestrator factory
  So that tutor_turn runs the full bounded revision loop with a real
    Coach (not the Phase-0 single-LLM shortcut), enforces the two-provider
    invariant at boot, and never leaks Coach free-text into the Player's
    revision channel.

  Background:
    Given the tutoring orchestrator surfaces (PlayerLike, CoachLike,
      PlayerCoachOrchestrator, validate_coach_config, parse_coach_output)
      are unchanged from Phase-0
    # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=high] D3 two-provider invariant: Coach provider
    # must differ from Player provider exactly (no canonicalisation)
    # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=high] Path C hybrid Coach: LLM emits per-criterion
    # JSON; deterministic post-processing assembles the CoachVerdict via
    # parse_coach_output
    And the AGENT_MODELS__REASONING_MODEL env var configures the Player provider
    And the AGENT_MODELS__COACH_MODEL env var configures the Coach provider
    And the LLMCoachAdapter parses LLM output via parse_coach_output

  # ==========================================================================
  # GROUP A: Key Examples
