  # Why: AC-LCA-08 — the two-provider invariant fails fast at boot, never
  # at first-turn, so an operator misconfig is visible before users connect.
  @task:TASK-LCA-004
  @negative @invariant @smoke
  Scenario: The MCP server refuses to boot when Player and Coach share a provider
    Given AGENT_MODELS__REASONING_MODEL and AGENT_MODELS__COACH_MODEL both
      resolve to the same provider
    When the MCPAdapter constructor runs the boot-time smoke check
    Then a CoachConfigurationError should be raised before the server serves any
      request
    And the error should name both providers
    And the error should reference the D3 two-provider invariant

  # Why: AC-LCA-07 — unset COACH_MODEL must be a clear configuration failure
  # at boot, not a default-to-Player silent failure.
