  # default; unset must raise at config-load (D-COACH-05)
  @task:TASK-LCA-004
  @negative @invariant
  Scenario: The Coach default model raises when the env var is unset
    Given AGENT_MODELS__COACH_MODEL is not set in the environment
    When the Coach default model resolver is called during orchestrator
      construction
    Then an LLMProviderError should be raised
    And the error should name the missing AGENT_MODELS__COACH_MODEL env var

  # Why: AC-LCA-06 — malformed Coach output must not crash the turn; the
  # orchestrator's unevaluated-turn fallback path is the safety net.
  @task:TASK-LCA-002
  @negative @fallback @smoke
  Scenario: A non-JSON Coach LLM response routes the turn to fallback
    Given an LLMCoachAdapter and a Coach LLM that returns a non-JSON string
    When the orchestrator asks the Coach to evaluate a Player response
    Then the Coach adapter should raise a malformed-Coach-output error
    And the orchestrator should route the turn to the unevaluated fallback path
    And the response decision should be fallback

  # Why: Coach JSON missing one or more required criteria is treated the
  # same as non-JSON — the verdict is not partially constructed.
  @task:TASK-LCA-002
  @negative @fallback
  Scenario: Coach JSON missing required criteria routes the turn to fallback
    Given an LLMCoachAdapter and a Coach LLM that returns JSON missing one of
      the six rubric criteria
    When the orchestrator asks the Coach to evaluate a Player response
    Then the Coach adapter should raise a malformed-Coach-output error
    And the orchestrator should route the turn to the unevaluated fallback path

  # Why: ASSUM-008 is the load-bearing safety boundary — Coach reasoning
  # must never appear inside the Player revision prompt under any condition.
  @task:TASK-LCA-001
  @negative @invariant @security
  Scenario: The Player revision prompt never carries Coach free-text reasoning
    Given the Coach has returned rubric feedback containing a free-text
