  # Why: AC-LCA-01 expansion — concurrent turns are the realistic load shape
  # for a single MCP server serving multiple learners; this is the test that
  # would surface a closure-capture bug.
  @task:TASK-LCA-005
  @edge-case @concurrency
  Scenario: Concurrent turns for distinct sessions get isolated orchestrators
    Given the MCP server is booted
    And two tutoring sessions are active for two different learners
    When both sessions invoke tutor_turn at the same time
    Then each invocation should construct its own orchestrator
    And the orchestrators should not share Player or Coach state
    And the responses should each carry the metadata of their own session only

  # Why: Coach transport failure (network, provider outage) is distinct from
  # malformed output but flows through the same orchestrator fallback.
  @task:TASK-LCA-002
  @edge-case @fallback
  Scenario: A Coach transport failure routes the turn to the unevaluated fallback
    Given an LLMCoachAdapter and a Coach LLM that raises a transport error
    When the orchestrator asks the Coach to evaluate a Player response
    Then the Coach adapter should surface a CoachUnavailableError
    And the orchestrator should route the turn to the unevaluated fallback path
    And the response decision should be fallback

